e-mail: gpet@rhi.hi.is
[Except for the absence of laminitis and this being the wrong time of year,
this seems a bit like the way Potomac Horse Fever, caused by _Ehrlichia
risticii_, showed up in the United States in the late 1970s. With the
popularity of Icelandic ponies these days, I'm sure the world horse owning
community appreciates the export ban. Please send any suggestion directly
to Dr. Petursson. - Mod.PC]
